   "source": [
    "# 🧠 Advanced Face Recognition System\n",
    "\n",
    "**Stack:**\n",
    "| Component | Technology | Why |\n",
    "|-----------|-----------|-----|\n",
    "| Detection | YuNet (DNN) | Fast, accurate, gives 5-point landmarks |\n",
    "| Recognition | SFace (DNN) | Deep embedding — far superior to LBPH |\n",
    "| Similarity | Cosine distance | Scale-invariant, works great with embeddings |\n",
    "| Preprocessing | CLAHE + alignment | Handles poor lighting & head tilt |\n",
    "| Augmentation | Flip, brightness, noise | More training signal from fewer photos |\n",
    "\n",
    "**How SFace works:**  \n",
    "Instead of hand-crafted texture patterns (LBPH), SFace runs each face through a deep neural network and produces a 128-dimensional embedding vector. Recognition = nearest neighbour search by cosine similarity. This is the same fundamental approach used in commercial face recognition systems."
   ]
  },
